      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "To achieve faster performance, we can use a manacher's algorithm, which is optimized for finding the longest palindromic substring. However, even this approach has a time complexity of O(n).\n\nHere's a modification of the previous code using Manacher's algorithm:\n\n```python\ndef longest_palindrome(s):\n    s = \"#\".join(\n        [\n            \"*\",\n            s + s[::-1],\n            \"*\",\n        ]\n    )\n    n = len(s)\n    p = [0] * n\n    c, r = 0, -1\n    center = 0\n    for i in range(1, n - 1):\n        if r > i:\n            i_mirror = 2 * c - i\n            p[i] = min(p[i_mirror], r - i + 1)\n        \n        while s[i + 1 + p[i]] == s[i - 1 - p[i]]:\n            p[i] += 1\n        \n        if i + p[i] > r:\n            c = i\n            r = i + p[i]\n            center = i\n    \n    res = \"\"\n    for i in range(n):\n        if p[i] > len(res):\n            res = s",
